# AI/RAG Lab

This document describes the planned AI and RAG experimentation environment.

## Purpose

The AI/RAG Lab will be used to experiment with Retrieval-Augmented Generation systems, vector databases, embeddings and knowledge base optimization.

This lab connects systems administration with artificial intelligence infrastructure.

## Planned Components

- Ubuntu Server
- PostgreSQL
- pgvector
- Embeddings service
- Python API
- Small knowledge base
- RAG prototype

## Example Architecture

```text
User Query
│
├── Backend API
│
├── Embeddings Service
│
├── Vector Database
│   └── PostgreSQL + pgvector
│
└── LLM Response
```

## Goals

- Understand how RAG systems work internally.
- Practice document structuring.
- Test semantic retrieval.
- Improve chunking strategies.
- Experiment with embeddings.
- Connect AI systems with infrastructure knowledge.
- Document retrieval problems and improvements.

## Planned Experiments

- Compare different document structures.
- Test query variations.
- Analyze retrieval quality.
- Evaluate wrong or missing answers.
- Build a small assistant using local infrastructure documentation.
- Test how small changes in documents affect retrieval results.

